The paper deals with a multiuser communication system with multiple antennas at the base station, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The use of regularized channel inversion as a precoding strategy suggests a focus on signal processing (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The problem of power allocation and user admission control also involves optimization (cs.MM).
